WEBVTT

00:02.260 --> 00:04.294
[ mid-tempo music playing ]

00:04.296 --> 00:06.463
Man: "the liberty report"
with sally langston.

00:06.465 --> 00:08.098
Two gifts have arrived,

00:08.100 --> 00:10.334
Addressed to you,
lovers of liberty.

00:10.336 --> 00:13.337
The first gift --
hollis doyle.

00:13.339 --> 00:16.273
The texas truth-teller is
throwing his hat into the ring.

00:16.275 --> 00:19.476
To which I say -- yee-haw!
Saddle up, little doggie.

00:19.478 --> 00:21.244
The second gift?

00:21.246 --> 00:22.813
Well, yours truly has agreed

00:22.815 --> 00:24.915
To host
the first republican debate --

00:24.917 --> 00:27.451
A duty I take very seriously,

00:27.453 --> 00:29.019
For debates mean setting aside

00:29.021 --> 00:30.821
Petty infighting
between the candidates

00:30.823 --> 00:32.289
And putting the lofty concerns

00:32.291 --> 00:34.591
Of the voters and the republic
above all.

00:34.593 --> 00:35.959
Olivia: Come on.

00:35.961 --> 00:37.260
You really think
it's okay for your network

00:37.262 --> 00:38.261
To allow hollis doyle's
super pac to advertise

00:38.263 --> 00:39.262
During the debate?

00:39.264 --> 00:40.263
We haven't decided
on super pacs.

00:40.265 --> 00:41.598
Hollis: The supreme court

00:41.600 --> 00:43.033
Calls that free speech,
livvie.
You may as well say,

00:43.035 --> 00:45.502
"this debate sponsored
by hollis doyle industries."

00:45.504 --> 00:46.470
Fine by me.
I can afford it.

00:46.472 --> 00:47.671
Are you sure
you don't want

00:47.673 --> 00:48.939
Your lawyer to represent you
in these negotiations,

00:48.941 --> 00:50.040
Mr. Doyle?

00:50.042 --> 00:51.608
Ain't nobody speaks better
for hollis doyle

00:51.610 --> 00:52.442
Than hollis doyle.

00:52.444 --> 00:53.477
Mnh-mnh.
No siree bob.

00:53.479 --> 00:54.511
Okay, fine.

00:54.513 --> 00:56.613
Bnc will ban
all candidates' super pacs

00:56.615 --> 00:57.681
From running ads.

00:57.683 --> 00:59.016
Now,
let's discuss podiums.

00:59.018 --> 01:00.951
We want clear, lucite.
Oh, no way.

01:00.953 --> 01:02.352
My candidate's
vertically challenged.

01:02.354 --> 01:03.387
She needs a box to stand on.

01:03.389 --> 01:04.721
And risk losing
that shorty vote?

01:04.723 --> 01:06.123
She can't use a box
if the podium is clear.

01:06.125 --> 01:07.491
That's all
people would talk about.

01:07.493 --> 01:08.825
I'd kill
for some of that shorty vote.

01:08.827 --> 01:10.060
The purpose
of this whole endeavor

01:10.062 --> 01:10.894
Is for the voters
to get a good, clear look

01:10.896 --> 01:12.229
At all the candidates.

01:12.231 --> 01:14.064
Oh, please. This is all about
showing off mellie's legs.

01:14.066 --> 01:15.132
Not at all.
[ scoffs ]

01:15.134 --> 01:17.734
Solid podium, 6-inch box.
Moving on.

01:17.736 --> 01:20.170
Whatever candidate is ahead
in the bnc poll

01:20.172 --> 01:21.972
Released 24 hours ahead
of the debate

01:21.974 --> 01:23.340
Is declared
the front-runner

01:23.342 --> 01:24.908
And gets the podium
at center stage.

01:24.910 --> 01:26.009
Your poll?

01:26.011 --> 01:27.244
You have a problem
with our polling?

01:27.246 --> 01:29.179
Your samples are tiny.
Your questions are vague.

01:29.181 --> 01:31.581
Frankly, your polling sucks.
She is right.

01:31.583 --> 01:33.050
It isn't reliable enough
to determine a front-runner.

01:33.052 --> 01:34.551
The stakes of who's at
the center podium are too high.

01:34.553 --> 01:38.188
We stand by our poll.
This point is not negotiable.

01:38.190 --> 01:40.590
We want a red light
indicating when time is up --

01:40.592 --> 01:42.392
A light and a buzzer.

01:42.394 --> 01:44.027
[ laughs ]

01:44.029 --> 01:45.662
Y'all think
some little toy buzzer's

01:45.664 --> 01:47.998
Gonna keep the truth
from tumbling from these jaws?

01:48.000 --> 01:49.499
I say,
good luck and godspeed.

01:49.501 --> 01:50.901
No light.
No buzzer.

01:50.903 --> 01:52.602
Then no mellie.

01:52.604 --> 01:54.571
Next issue --
opening statements.

01:54.573 --> 01:55.739
Did you hear me?

01:55.741 --> 01:57.007
I'm pulling my candidate.

01:57.009 --> 01:59.409
Whoa! That's some sore losin'
right there.

01:59.411 --> 02:01.211
It's no secret that sally
and hollis are friends.

02:01.213 --> 02:02.712
If there's no buzzer,
no blinking light,

02:02.714 --> 02:04.714
She'll let him run wild,
fill all the air time.

02:04.716 --> 02:06.283
I'm sorry --
no light, no buzzer.

02:06.285 --> 02:07.918
Then this debate is biased
before it begins.

02:07.920 --> 02:08.785
We're out.

02:08.787 --> 02:10.420
Olivia, don't.
[ chuckles ]

02:10.422 --> 02:11.755
Elizabeth: Save it, richard.
She's just posturing.

02:11.757 --> 02:14.057
I'm pulling mellie,
and auctioning off

02:14.059 --> 02:16.426
A one-hour exclusive interview
with her

02:16.428 --> 02:17.961
To your competition.

02:17.963 --> 02:20.030
And whichever network gives me
the most favorable terms

02:20.032 --> 02:21.264
Gets to air that interview
live --

02:21.266 --> 02:22.699
Go head-to-head
with your debate

02:22.701 --> 02:25.035
And spend the hour
slamming bnc's blatant bias

02:25.037 --> 02:27.104
While sucking
half your ratings.

02:27.106 --> 02:29.206
Good luck explaining that
to your advertisers.

02:29.208 --> 02:31.174
Ms. Pope...

02:36.214 --> 02:38.215
How'd it go?

02:38.217 --> 02:39.149
Just wait.

02:39.151 --> 02:40.083
I don't...

02:40.085 --> 02:40.984
Why are you smiling?

02:40.986 --> 02:42.586
Just wait.

02:42.588 --> 02:46.089
5, 4, 3, 2, 1...

02:46.091 --> 02:47.991
Okay, olivia.
Lights and buzzers.

02:47.993 --> 02:49.059
Of my choosing.

02:49.061 --> 02:50.227
Fine.

02:50.229 --> 02:51.595
Good.

02:51.597 --> 02:53.663
Now, about those podiums.

03:02.073 --> 03:03.940
Susan: What you're suggesting,
mr. Doyle --

03:03.942 --> 03:05.809
That's not
an immigration policy,

03:05.811 --> 03:07.344
It's institutionalized
racism.

03:07.346 --> 03:09.346
Now, hold on a minute.
If we close our borders --

03:09.348 --> 03:12.983
Do you have any idea how much
of our economy depends

03:12.985 --> 03:15.252
On the ideas and contributions
of non-citizens?

03:15.254 --> 03:17.254
The best young minds
in the world,

03:17.256 --> 03:19.823
They come here,
they enroll in our universities,

03:19.825 --> 03:21.591
And once they graduate,
they stay.

03:21.593 --> 03:23.693
And we want them to stay.

03:23.695 --> 03:27.030
They become our engineers,
our doctors, our scientists.

03:27.032 --> 03:29.766
Immigration isn't a curse,
mr. Doyle.

03:29.768 --> 03:32.602
It's the key
to staying competitive.

03:32.604 --> 03:33.537
How was that?

03:33.539 --> 03:34.871
Elizabeth: Good.

03:34.873 --> 03:37.340
Excellent, actually.

03:37.342 --> 03:39.676
She's knocking it
out of the park.

03:39.678 --> 03:41.945
Climate change, immigration,
reproductive rights.

03:41.947 --> 03:42.879
You're trying
to psych me out.

03:42.881 --> 03:44.481
I'm trying to recruit you.

03:44.483 --> 03:47.551
Susan is the real deal, liv --
smart, passionate.

03:47.553 --> 03:48.685
Relatable?

03:48.687 --> 03:50.387
You say that so longingly.

03:50.389 --> 03:52.389
Is mellie --
being mellie?

03:52.391 --> 03:54.157
Yes.
I can't -- I won't...

03:54.159 --> 03:56.393
I guarantee you
there is no one on this planet

03:56.395 --> 03:58.361
As stubborn and as arrogant
and as big a pain in the ass

03:58.363 --> 03:59.863
As mellie grant.

03:59.865 --> 04:04.467
And yet, somehow, I think
she'd make a great president.

04:04.469 --> 04:05.735
Is that crazy?

04:05.737 --> 04:07.204
Yes.
Yes, it is, liv.

04:07.206 --> 04:10.040
Speaking of wannabe presidents,
you've heard the rumors?

04:11.209 --> 04:12.209
I have.

04:12.211 --> 04:14.344
Well? Is it true?
I don't know.

04:14.346 --> 04:16.179
If anyone knew, it'd be you.
Aren't you curious?

04:16.181 --> 04:18.982
I'm looking into it.

04:21.852 --> 04:23.053
So, are you
running for president?

04:23.055 --> 04:24.521
How'd you hear?

04:24.523 --> 04:26.056
You should announce.

04:26.058 --> 04:27.924
I'm announcing
in the morning.

04:27.926 --> 04:29.426
Before I do,
I wanted to check in with you

04:29.428 --> 04:30.827
About meridian terrace
about meridian terrace.

04:32.263 --> 04:33.163
Don't worry about it.

04:33.165 --> 04:34.497
It's just,
once I announce,

04:34.499 --> 04:36.866
My enemies will dig deeper
than ever before.

04:36.868 --> 04:40.270
Edison,
don't worry about it.

04:40.272 --> 04:41.738
You vouched for me
on national television.

04:41.740 --> 04:43.840
I owe you.

04:45.843 --> 04:46.676
Thank you, liv.

04:46.678 --> 04:47.844
Mm-hmm.

04:50.548 --> 04:52.015
Edison?

04:53.451 --> 04:56.453
You'll be
a great candidate.

04:56.455 --> 04:59.556
Thanks.

04:59.558 --> 05:02.225
I figure it's about time we had
our first black president.

05:02.227 --> 05:04.527
Mm.

05:04.529 --> 05:06.997
It's about time we had
our first <i>woman</i> president.

05:08.599 --> 05:10.100
[ both chuckle ]

05:12.036 --> 05:13.403
Good luck
in the election.

05:13.405 --> 05:15.839
You, too.

05:19.910 --> 05:21.945
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

05:23.781 --> 05:25.548
David: Help me.

05:25.550 --> 05:27.484
Oh! David!
What the hell?

05:27.486 --> 05:29.085
I'm sorry.
I needed someone to talk to,

05:29.087 --> 05:31.254
And you're the only one
I can talk to about this.

05:31.256 --> 05:32.989
"this" as in the two women
you're still seeing?

05:32.991 --> 05:34.090
It's an addiction.

05:34.092 --> 05:35.558
David, I don't have time.

05:35.560 --> 05:37.627
With one woman --
the good woman --

05:37.629 --> 05:39.396
The sex is
good, intimate.

05:39.398 --> 05:40.930
Stop talking

05:40.932 --> 05:42.932
But with the other woman --
the nasty woman --

05:42.934 --> 05:44.100
The sex is...

05:44.102 --> 05:46.303
Well, it's still good,
but it's <i>nasty.</i>

05:46.305 --> 05:47.137
Not listening.

05:47.139 --> 05:48.571
The things she does,
abby --

05:48.573 --> 05:50.974
The vile, awful things --
the biting --

05:50.976 --> 05:52.275
Okay.
This is harassment!

05:52.277 --> 05:53.977
It's starting
to affect my work.

05:53.979 --> 05:55.745
I'm zoning out
all the time.

05:55.747 --> 05:57.447
I'm forgetting
important details.

05:57.449 --> 05:59.416
How is the attorney general
of the United States

05:59.418 --> 06:00.517
Supposed to do his job

06:00.519 --> 06:02.585
When he's in some weird,
dirty sex trance?

06:02.587 --> 06:03.620
You stop seeing her.

06:03.622 --> 06:04.821
Which her?
I don't care.

06:04.823 --> 06:06.189
I need your help.
Help me choose.

06:06.191 --> 06:07.390
Get out!

06:09.593 --> 06:11.361
Rosen.

06:11.363 --> 06:12.996
In here -- now.

06:15.933 --> 06:17.400
[ door opens ]

06:19.303 --> 06:20.103
David.

06:20.105 --> 06:21.671
Oh.
Hi, susan.

06:21.673 --> 06:23.373
Sit.

06:23.375 --> 06:25.308
I asked david
to join us this morning

06:25.310 --> 06:27.110
Because there's something
we need to discuss.

06:27.112 --> 06:28.645
Okay.

06:28.647 --> 06:31.314
People have started
asking questions about
your personal life.

06:31.316 --> 06:33.783
They're speculating
in an effort to relate to you,

06:33.785 --> 06:35.218
Identify with you.

06:35.220 --> 06:36.920
They're wondering if
you've found someone special.

06:38.322 --> 06:39.956
Okay...

06:39.958 --> 06:41.891
I think it's time
we tell the world that you have.

06:41.893 --> 06:44.828
The two of you need to come out
as a public couple --

06:44.830 --> 06:46.563
After the debate,
on-stage.

06:46.565 --> 06:48.498
When the families come up
to hug their candidates,

06:48.500 --> 06:51.101
David needs to come up
and hug you, susan.

06:52.737 --> 06:54.871
[ stammers ]
elizabeth.

06:54.873 --> 06:57.640
That is -- that is a lot
to ask of a person.

06:57.642 --> 06:58.875
Elizabeth: David,
do you have a problem

06:58.877 --> 07:00.877
Going up on-stage
after the debate?

07:04.582 --> 07:06.383
David,
you don't need to answer that.

07:06.385 --> 07:08.017
I'll do it.

07:08.019 --> 07:09.052
After the debates,

07:09.054 --> 07:11.888
I'll come up on-stage
with you -- for you.

07:11.890 --> 07:14.591
I'll do it, susan.
I want to do it.

07:14.593 --> 07:15.392
I choose to do it.

07:15.394 --> 07:16.826
Okay, then.

07:16.828 --> 07:18.161
I'll let the press know
it's happening.

07:25.770 --> 07:27.404
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

07:27.406 --> 07:29.172
Cyrus: Name of the game
is messaging.

07:29.174 --> 07:32.876
We're not just <i>selling</i>
<i>frankie vargas.</i>

07:32.878 --> 07:36.346
We're offering a product.
We're offering belief.

07:36.348 --> 07:38.915
We're offering
a chance for something better.

07:38.917 --> 07:41.251
Connect with frankie,
believe in frankie.

07:41.253 --> 07:43.853
And you get...Better.

07:43.855 --> 07:45.588
Now, we have the message.

07:45.590 --> 07:49.626
Next question is, how do we
communicate it to the people?

07:49.628 --> 07:50.927
Alex: Excuse me.

07:50.929 --> 07:53.263
I like that logo.
It's nice, polished.

07:53.265 --> 07:55.131
But, come November,
we're not counting the people

07:55.133 --> 07:56.900
Who like our artwork
or our slogan.

07:56.902 --> 07:58.201
We're counting votes.
Yes. I'll get to that.

07:58.203 --> 07:59.903
And we know
how to turn out votes,

07:59.905 --> 08:01.204
Don't we,
my frankie friends?

08:01.206 --> 08:02.739
[ applause ]
all right,
to turn out votes,

08:02.741 --> 08:05.108
We've got to take it
to the streets, right?

08:05.110 --> 08:07.877
Win them one by one -- just like
we did in pittsburgh in 2010.

08:07.879 --> 08:09.145
Don't forget scranton.

08:09.147 --> 08:10.880
How could I
[chuckling] emily?

08:10.882 --> 08:11.948
How could any of us,
right?

08:11.950 --> 08:14.551
It was 10 below,
sleet in our faces,

08:14.553 --> 08:16.653
Getting those buses
of elderly and disabled folks

08:16.655 --> 08:18.288
To their polling places.
Yeah!

08:18.290 --> 08:19.556
See,
we got to take that spirit...

08:19.558 --> 08:20.557
[ cheers and applause ]
...And multiply it.

08:20.559 --> 08:22.225
All right?
Share our commitment.

08:22.227 --> 08:23.827
Share the love we have
for frankie vargas

08:23.829 --> 08:25.295
With the good people
of iowa.

08:25.297 --> 08:26.729
[ cheers and applause ]

08:26.731 --> 08:28.298
And new hampshire!

08:28.300 --> 08:30.567
[ cheers grow louder ]
and every single state!

08:30.569 --> 08:33.603
Until it's 10 below again,
sleet in our faces.

08:33.605 --> 08:34.637
But this time?

08:34.639 --> 08:36.606
This time,
we're in washington, d.C.

08:36.608 --> 08:37.807
[ cheers and applause ]

08:37.809 --> 08:39.809
On the steps of the capitol,

08:39.811 --> 08:42.912
Watching my brother sworn in

08:42.914 --> 08:45.849
As the next president
of the United States.

08:45.851 --> 08:47.250
[ cheers and applause ]

08:47.252 --> 08:49.352
[ laughs ]

08:50.421 --> 08:52.856
Hey. Alex vargas.
And you are?

09:01.432 --> 09:02.799
Frankie: He's my brother.
Cyrus: Yes, I know that.

09:02.801 --> 09:03.500
So, what's the problem?

09:03.502 --> 09:05.101
The problem, governor,

09:05.103 --> 09:08.004
Is that I'm running
your campaign for <i>president,</i>

09:08.006 --> 09:10.006
And if your brother doesn't
respect that, or worse,

09:10.008 --> 09:11.274
Thinks he's in charge
[chuckles] --

09:11.276 --> 09:12.475
He knows
you're in charge.

09:12.477 --> 09:13.776
Yes, but I'm not sure
he likes it.

09:15.946 --> 09:18.047
He's my brother.

09:18.049 --> 09:19.349
You really have a problem
with my brother?

09:20.317 --> 09:21.317
No.

09:21.319 --> 09:23.553
Good.

09:23.555 --> 09:24.120
Glad we're
on the same page.

09:27.791 --> 09:28.958
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

09:28.960 --> 09:30.627
I just don't like her.

09:30.629 --> 09:32.529
Smug -- that's the word.

09:32.531 --> 09:34.030
Smug and arrogant.

09:34.032 --> 09:36.165
And I hated
the way she said...

09:36.167 --> 09:38.468
Divisive. It's such
an inside-the-beltway term.

09:38.470 --> 09:39.636
You know what I mean?

09:39.638 --> 09:41.738
That hair --
makes me miss my soaps.

09:41.740 --> 09:44.307
I liked her book,
but when she starts talking...

09:44.309 --> 09:46.910
Yeah. She might be okay
if she didn't talk.

09:46.912 --> 09:49.579
She seems, I don't know,
like, too smart or something.

09:51.348 --> 09:52.649
"too smart"?

09:52.651 --> 09:53.750
Well,
don't take it literally.

09:53.752 --> 09:55.184
Their feedback
all made the same point.

09:55.186 --> 09:57.921
We can't base
a national strategy off them.

09:57.923 --> 09:59.155
They're not as stupid
as you think.

09:59.157 --> 10:00.990
Maybe they sense
your...Disdain.

10:00.992 --> 10:02.659
Shut up.
Mellie.

10:02.661 --> 10:04.027
My ideas are good.

10:04.029 --> 10:05.895
I am addressing the issues
they say are important to them.

10:05.897 --> 10:08.698
That's true, but you come off
as aloof, out-of-touch.

10:08.700 --> 10:10.433
I'm neither of those things.

10:10.435 --> 10:11.901
How much does a gallon of gas
cost -- national average?

10:11.903 --> 10:13.369
$2.02.

10:13.371 --> 10:14.537
That's right.

10:14.539 --> 10:16.072
Of course it's right.

10:16.074 --> 10:18.074
I can give you the average price
in every state if you like --

10:18.076 --> 10:19.576
Regular or diesel.

10:19.578 --> 10:21.678
I can also tell you
that if we keep the gas tax

10:21.680 --> 10:23.713
At the absurdly low rate
of 18 cents a gallon,

10:23.715 --> 10:25.248
The highway trust fund
will run out of money

10:25.250 --> 10:26.883
By the middle of next year.
And right there --

10:26.885 --> 10:27.951
That's the problem.
What?

10:27.953 --> 10:29.218
You're a know-it-all,
mellie.

10:29.220 --> 10:30.186
So?

10:30.188 --> 10:31.721
So,
the people in that room

10:31.723 --> 10:33.122
Are the same people who are
gonna be watching the debate,

10:33.124 --> 10:34.457
Who are gonna
go to the polls,

10:34.459 --> 10:35.892
Who are gonna be electing
our next president.

10:35.894 --> 10:37.594
And they aren't gonna
vote for you

10:37.596 --> 10:38.595
If they get the feeling
that you think you're smarter

10:38.597 --> 10:39.762
Than everybody else.

10:39.764 --> 10:41.297
I am fighting
their fight, liv.

10:41.299 --> 10:43.399
I'm just fighting it
as a rhodes scholar.

10:43.401 --> 10:46.035
They are benefiting
from how smart I am.

10:46.037 --> 10:49.973
And now I'm supposed
to...Dumb it down?

10:56.814 --> 10:59.015
[ sighs ]

11:01.785 --> 11:04.988
Mellie grant --
woman of the people.

11:04.990 --> 11:06.723
[ knock on door ]
fine.

11:11.595 --> 11:13.096
[ door closes ]

11:13.098 --> 11:14.664
I'm letting other people's
security cameras

11:14.666 --> 11:16.399
Do the work for us.
Any anomalies?

11:16.401 --> 11:18.334
He heads to work at 7:00,
eats most of his lunches there,

11:18.336 --> 11:20.336
Goes to the white house,
sometimes langley.

11:20.338 --> 11:22.271
Then, around 7:30 or 8:00,
he's back in his car

11:22.273 --> 11:23.673
And either joining your father
for a late dinner

11:23.675 --> 11:25.108
Or heading home
to blondie.

11:25.110 --> 11:27.477
He's using her for something.
I just can't figure out what.

11:27.479 --> 11:29.579
I can keep tracking him
like this, if you want.

11:29.581 --> 11:31.280
It's perfectly untraceable --
that's the good news.

11:31.282 --> 11:33.182
The bad news is...
It's not enough.

11:33.184 --> 11:34.317
Mnh-mnh.
[ sighs ]

11:34.319 --> 11:35.318
Plan "b"?

11:35.320 --> 11:36.853
Plan "b."

11:36.855 --> 11:38.321
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

11:38.323 --> 11:40.156
Vanessa: So, the main point
of the article

11:40.158 --> 11:42.458
Is that women need
to stop apologizing for

11:42.460 --> 11:44.360
Well, basically,
just giving our opinions.

11:44.362 --> 11:45.294
Woman: Vanessa moss?

11:45.296 --> 11:47.096
Yes?

11:47.098 --> 11:49.265
Uh, we went to college together
at smith.

11:49.267 --> 11:50.333
Jacqueline horton.

11:50.335 --> 11:52.769
Nice to meet you,
jacqueline.

11:52.771 --> 11:54.270
[ chuckles ]

11:54.272 --> 11:55.938
Wow, I can't believe
you recognized me.

11:55.940 --> 11:57.106
God, are you kidding?

11:57.108 --> 11:59.208
You were the star
of the english department.

11:59.210 --> 12:00.777
Your poetry
was legendary.

12:00.779 --> 12:02.345
That seems like
a lifetime ago.

12:02.347 --> 12:04.814
I can't remember the last time
I wrote something.

12:04.816 --> 12:06.215
Well, besides a briefing.

12:06.217 --> 12:08.317
Oh, my god -- that ring.

12:08.319 --> 12:09.819
[ gasps ]
your guy did good.

12:09.821 --> 12:11.554
Yeah.
Jake's pretty amazing.

12:11.556 --> 12:13.356
So, tell me everything.

12:13.358 --> 12:16.559
Where and when, deejay or band,
casual or black tie?

12:16.561 --> 12:18.561
Oh. Um, we haven't really nailed
down all the details yet.

12:18.563 --> 12:21.964
Oh, if you want, I have tons of
wedding books I could give you.

12:21.966 --> 12:24.333
[ gasps ] oh,
and my photographer was a dream.

12:24.335 --> 12:26.135
He even made my mother-in-law
look like an angel.

12:26.137 --> 12:27.003
Really?
Mm-hmm.

12:27.005 --> 12:28.004
[ chuckles ]
I would love that.

12:28.006 --> 12:29.572
That is so sweet of you,
jacqueline.

12:29.574 --> 12:30.840
Are you kidding?
It's my pleasure.

12:30.842 --> 12:31.974
So, what does
your schedule look like

12:31.976 --> 12:32.975
For the rest of the week?

12:36.880 --> 12:39.148
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

12:39.150 --> 12:40.316
[ door opens ]
susan.

12:40.318 --> 12:41.584
Hey.

12:41.586 --> 12:42.885
Just wanted to thank you

12:42.887 --> 12:44.020
For clearing
the president's schedule.

12:44.022 --> 12:45.254
Oh, it was nothing.

12:45.256 --> 12:46.689
What you should really
thank me for

12:46.691 --> 12:49.025
Is convincing him
not to do hollis' accent.

12:49.027 --> 12:50.560
I heard him practicing
in the oval.

12:50.562 --> 12:52.762
It was dreadful.
[ both chuckle ]

12:54.398 --> 12:55.631
Is this...

12:55.633 --> 12:57.600
Does this belong to --
oh, it's david rosen's.

12:57.602 --> 13:00.002
He stops by,
complains about

13:00.004 --> 13:02.538
The difficulties
of juggling his women.

13:02.540 --> 13:03.773
At first I thought he was
trying to make me jealous --

13:03.775 --> 13:05.508
I'm sorry.
"women"?

13:05.510 --> 13:08.077
Yeah. He's got a couple of them,
apparently -- super annoying.

13:08.079 --> 13:09.212
A couple of <i>women?</i>

13:09.214 --> 13:10.580
I've gotten pretty good
at tuning him out.

13:10.582 --> 13:12.048
Anyway, thanks.

13:12.050 --> 13:14.817
I'm afraid he'll be back
all too soon to get this.

13:17.721 --> 13:18.955
Elizabeth:
Madam vice president?

13:18.957 --> 13:20.456
[ sighs ]

13:20.458 --> 13:23.092
Madam vi-- susan!
Hey.

13:23.094 --> 13:24.761
I'm sorry.

13:24.763 --> 13:26.229
Uh, what was
the question again?

13:26.231 --> 13:28.197
[ sighs ]
committing troops.

13:28.199 --> 13:31.768
Right. Well,
the situation in kashfar --

13:31.770 --> 13:32.802
Bandar.

13:32.804 --> 13:34.203
Bandar, right.
[ chuckles ]

13:34.205 --> 13:36.038
I always get
those two women confused.

13:36.040 --> 13:36.973
"women"?

13:36.975 --> 13:38.708
What?
[ sighs ]

13:38.710 --> 13:40.610
You said, "I always get
those two women confused."

13:40.612 --> 13:41.811
Oh.

13:41.813 --> 13:44.247
[ laughing ]
I meant countries.

13:44.249 --> 13:46.616
[ "boogie wonderland"
by earth, wind & fire playing ]

13:46.618 --> 13:48.618
