[ camera shutters clicking ]

13:48.620 --> 13:50.319
Debate prep is for ninnies.

13:51.722 --> 13:54.123
Only thing ol' hollis needs

13:54.125 --> 13:57.660
Is eight hours of sleep
and a good, hearty breakfast.

13:57.662 --> 13:59.629
â™ª boogie wonderland

13:59.631 --> 14:01.597
[ chuckles ]

14:01.599 --> 14:04.267
Mr. Doyle has decided that
he doesn't want to pay taxes.

14:04.269 --> 14:06.736
That's why he sets up
his companies overseas.

14:06.738 --> 14:08.070
Olivia:
Lose the bitch face.

14:10.073 --> 14:11.574
[ clears throat ]

14:11.576 --> 14:12.508
Mr. Doyle has decided
he doesn't --

14:12.510 --> 14:13.576
Still bitch face.

14:13.578 --> 14:14.644
I'm smiling.

14:14.646 --> 14:16.312
Yeah. Like you're better
than everybody else.

14:16.314 --> 14:17.780
[ sighs ]

14:17.782 --> 14:20.283
â™ª stares you in the face

14:20.285 --> 14:23.686
â™ª and says, "baby, uh, uh,
it don't work" â™ª

14:23.688 --> 14:25.855
[ gunshots ]

14:25.857 --> 14:27.323
â™ª you don't care

14:27.325 --> 14:30.493
â™ª you dance and shake the hurt

14:30.495 --> 14:32.595
[ gunfire ]

14:32.597 --> 14:34.797
â™ª boogie wonderland

14:34.799 --> 14:36.799
[ chuckles ]

14:36.801 --> 14:38.201
I don't know
what you want.

14:38.203 --> 14:39.535
I want filibuster mellie.
Where's that mellie?

14:39.537 --> 14:40.703
That's who america loves.

14:40.705 --> 14:42.104
That's who
they want to vote for.

14:42.106 --> 14:44.207
The mellie who takes off her
shoes and eats a protein bar.

14:44.209 --> 14:45.474
I had been on my feet
all day.

14:45.476 --> 14:46.876
I was tired and hungry,
and I had to pee.

14:46.878 --> 14:48.110
I was practically feral.

14:48.112 --> 14:49.645
You were human.
[ scoffs ]

14:49.647 --> 14:51.113
Also,
you need to watch your arms.

14:51.115 --> 14:52.148
I'm using less arms.

14:52.150 --> 14:53.049
Use a little less
than that.

14:53.051 --> 14:54.550
[ sighs ]

14:54.552 --> 14:59.188
â™ª when I start to dance
in boogie wonderland â™ª

14:59.190 --> 15:00.356
â™ª dance
[ camera shutter clicking ]

15:00.358 --> 15:02.325
â™ª I find romance
[ chuckles ]

15:02.327 --> 15:03.392
Come on.

15:03.394 --> 15:04.827
Come on, don't be shy.

15:04.829 --> 15:06.395
Mmm-mmm-mmm.

15:06.397 --> 15:09.966
â™ª the love

15:09.968 --> 15:11.133
Mmm.

15:11.135 --> 15:12.468
Smoky.

15:12.470 --> 15:17.540
Senator grant has missed
127 votes since being in office.

15:17.542 --> 15:19.175
[ scoffs ]
that's 24%.

15:19.177 --> 15:20.843
35%.

15:20.845 --> 15:22.311
24 is the number
of epa sanctions

15:22.313 --> 15:24.046
Leveled against
doyle energy last year.

15:24.048 --> 15:25.214
Let's start again.

15:25.216 --> 15:27.850
Did you break susan?

15:27.852 --> 15:30.219
Because your girlfriend
is in a death spiral.

15:30.221 --> 15:32.555
Just fix it, okay?

15:32.557 --> 15:34.190
"pencils down."

15:34.192 --> 15:36.492
We all remember
those dreaded words from school.

15:36.494 --> 15:38.928
When you heard them,
it meant you were out of time.

15:38.930 --> 15:40.563
That's a feeling our
republican presidential hopefuls

15:40.565 --> 15:42.198
Can relate to.

15:42.200 --> 15:43.933
With only two days left
before their first debate,

15:43.935 --> 15:45.434
They're cramming like crazy

15:45.436 --> 15:49.005
In preparation for the most
important test of their lives --

15:49.007 --> 15:51.107
A test,
my dear lovers of liberty,

15:51.109 --> 15:52.842
That you will be grading.

15:52.844 --> 15:53.943
Oh, and it will be tough one.

15:53.945 --> 15:54.944
How do I know?

15:54.946 --> 15:56.946
Because I'm writing it.

16:03.020 --> 16:04.086
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

16:04.088 --> 16:06.622
[ footsteps approach ]

16:06.624 --> 16:07.757
Wedding books?

16:07.759 --> 16:08.858
Something
you want to tell me?

16:08.860 --> 16:10.393
They're for vanessa.

16:10.395 --> 16:11.928
I told her
I got married last month.

16:11.930 --> 16:13.262
We're meeting
for drinks later

16:13.264 --> 16:14.931
So I can share
my extensive bridal knowledge.

16:14.933 --> 16:15.965
Good. The more
you get to know her,

16:15.967 --> 16:17.066
The better our chances are

16:17.068 --> 16:18.267
Of finding out
what her value is to jake.

16:18.269 --> 16:20.770
Alex: Olivia pope.

16:20.772 --> 16:22.805
Can I help you?

16:22.807 --> 16:23.906
Alejandro vargas.

16:23.908 --> 16:24.907
Hm.

16:24.909 --> 16:26.475
How can I help you,
mr. Vargas?

16:26.477 --> 16:28.244
Alex. I'm sure
you're pretty busy --

16:28.246 --> 16:29.779
I <i>am</i> pretty busy.
No doubt.

16:29.781 --> 16:30.947
Alex: I'm helping my brother,
frankie, with his campaign.

16:30.949 --> 16:32.048
I'm not here
to talk about him.

16:32.050 --> 16:33.916
I'm here to help you
with senator grant.

16:33.918 --> 16:35.885
I think I can handle that
on my own.

16:35.887 --> 16:37.119
Thanks, though.

16:37.121 --> 16:39.155
Well, this is dirt
on susan ross.

16:40.424 --> 16:42.091
Ah.

16:42.093 --> 16:44.260
That look in your eye
is priceless.

16:44.262 --> 16:45.728
You got to love politics.

16:45.730 --> 16:47.496
Let me guess.

16:47.498 --> 16:50.232
You scratch my back,
I scratch yours?

16:50.234 --> 16:52.868
You give me that envelope if I
give you dirt on edison davis?

16:54.504 --> 16:55.504
I love your shop.

16:55.506 --> 16:56.739
Did you and cyrus
cook that up?

16:56.741 --> 16:58.240
I'm not your adversary.

16:58.242 --> 16:59.675
We trade dirt,
I win the democratic primary,

16:59.677 --> 17:00.576
You win the republican,

17:00.578 --> 17:01.978
Then we become
adversaries.

17:01.980 --> 17:04.313
Hmm. Sorry, mr. Vargas.
I don't play dirty.

17:04.315 --> 17:06.415
Uh, should you
change your mind --

17:06.417 --> 17:09.318
I just air dropped you
my contact info.

17:09.320 --> 17:10.586
[ cellphone beeps ]

17:18.462 --> 17:20.196
Huck:
Alex vargas -- 42, single,

17:20.198 --> 17:22.264
Has run every one of
his older brother's campaigns

17:22.266 --> 17:23.199
And won them all.

17:23.201 --> 17:25.434
Impressive.
How does he do it?

17:25.436 --> 17:26.602
Well...

17:26.604 --> 17:28.037
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

17:28.039 --> 17:30.206
By any means necessary.

17:30.208 --> 17:33.342
They just win -- dirt,
intimidation, connections.

17:33.344 --> 17:35.444
Alex is wildly loyal
to his brother.

17:35.446 --> 17:37.780
He cold-cocked a councilman
in city hall

17:37.782 --> 17:39.482
When he called frankie "amigo"
in an interview.

17:39.484 --> 17:41.017
[ sighs ]

17:41.019 --> 17:42.651
I've been going over
this mellie stuff we shot.

17:42.653 --> 17:43.986
I know she's working hard at it,
but --

17:43.988 --> 17:45.154
She's still
no woman of the people?

17:45.156 --> 17:46.355
I think we need to do
another focus group.

17:46.357 --> 17:47.390
We don't have time.

17:47.392 --> 17:49.492
Hollis is stealing
all the news cycles.

17:49.494 --> 17:51.827
We've got to get mellie out
in public before the debate,

17:51.829 --> 17:53.029
Or all sally's questions
are gonna be

17:53.031 --> 17:55.564
About why she's hiding
from the electorate.

17:55.566 --> 17:56.665
The gettysburger test?

17:56.667 --> 17:58.734
The gettysburger test.

17:58.736 --> 18:00.536
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>
<i>[ foxy's "get off" plays ]</i>

18:00.538 --> 18:02.304
Welcome to gettysbur--
thank you.

18:02.306 --> 18:03.539
Oh, my god.

18:03.541 --> 18:04.473
[ mellie chuckles ]

18:04.475 --> 18:06.208
Hi, there.

18:06.210 --> 18:07.476
Hello. Hi.

18:07.478 --> 18:08.511
Oh, oh. Hi, sir.
Oh!

18:08.513 --> 18:09.512
[ chuckles ]

18:09.514 --> 18:10.813
[ exhales ]

18:10.815 --> 18:13.082
Oh, you can go on up front,
ma'am.

18:13.084 --> 18:14.150
Oh, heavens, no.

18:14.152 --> 18:15.518
I can wait my turn
like everybody else.

18:15.520 --> 18:17.853
[ chuckles ]

18:17.855 --> 18:20.256
Mellie: A hat? Really?

18:20.258 --> 18:22.258
Really. We're beating hollis
at his own game, mellie --

18:22.260 --> 18:23.993
Offering up
the picture-perfect image

18:23.995 --> 18:25.861
Of a down-home, relatable,
approachable candidate

18:25.863 --> 18:27.430
People will want
to vote for.

18:27.432 --> 18:29.098
You go in there,
you stand in line,

18:29.100 --> 18:30.166
And you place your order.

18:30.168 --> 18:32.935
I'm thinking
a double lincoln with cheese.

18:32.937 --> 18:34.336
Double lincoln with cheese,
please.

18:34.338 --> 18:35.671
And don't forget about
the little round topper.

18:35.673 --> 18:37.573
Nice.

18:37.575 --> 18:39.275
After that, you find a booth on
the east side of the restaurant

18:39.277 --> 18:41.343
By the windows -- that's
the best spot for the cameras.

18:41.345 --> 18:42.344
What if all the booths
are taken?

18:42.346 --> 18:43.179
Even better.

18:43.181 --> 18:45.281
You join
whoever's sitting there.

18:45.283 --> 18:46.449
You keep
the conversation light,

18:46.451 --> 18:48.050
And you enjoy the hell
out of your meal.

18:48.052 --> 18:49.518
Just make sure you finish
the entire thing.

18:49.520 --> 18:51.387
You skipped breakfast,
right?

18:51.389 --> 18:53.923
Senator, when's the last time
you ate at a gettysburger?

18:53.925 --> 18:56.058
Oh, I must admit,
it's been a little while.

18:56.060 --> 18:57.726
[ chuckles ]

18:57.728 --> 18:59.762
Are you enjoying your freedom
fries as much as I am, billy?

18:59.764 --> 19:01.397
So you've been
to a gettysburger before, then?

19:01.399 --> 19:03.532
What kind of american would I be
if I hadn't, jim?

19:03.534 --> 19:04.767
Which location?

19:04.769 --> 19:05.968
What?

19:05.970 --> 19:07.803
Which location
have you been to?

19:10.874 --> 19:11.807
Ooh.

19:13.877 --> 19:15.878
Federal triangle, usually.

19:15.880 --> 19:18.547
Or 21st and q.
You know the one?

19:18.549 --> 19:20.249
It's in the shopping mall
there on the third floor.

19:20.251 --> 19:21.717
You have to really look
for that one, though.

19:21.719 --> 19:24.587
It's right next
to the carousel.

19:24.589 --> 19:26.122
Karen and I used to stop in
every Sunday.

19:26.124 --> 19:28.324
It's the one
closest to our church.

19:28.326 --> 19:30.159
Uh, I'm sorry, you said you
used to stop in every Sunday?

19:30.161 --> 19:32.394
Like clockwork --
right after services.

19:32.396 --> 19:33.729
But...

19:33.731 --> 19:35.831
Gettysburger's closed
on sundays.

19:35.833 --> 19:38.300
In honor of the first
major battle of the civil war --

19:38.302 --> 19:40.002
Happened on a Sunday.

19:40.004 --> 19:41.770
I thought everybody
knew that.

19:41.772 --> 19:43.639
[ camera shutters clicking ]

19:46.843 --> 19:47.843
It's burgergate!

19:47.845 --> 19:49.678
Oh, come on.
She was mistaken.

19:49.680 --> 19:51.413
She was lying!

19:51.415 --> 19:53.082
That woman hasn't ever
stepped foot in a gettysburger,

19:53.084 --> 19:54.183
And she knows it.

19:54.185 --> 19:55.317
Out of all the things
to lie about, hank,

19:55.319 --> 19:56.819
Why would she lie
about eating a burger?

19:56.821 --> 19:58.487
Because she knows she's got
to soften her image, brooke.

19:58.489 --> 19:59.955
Mellie grant's an ice queen.

19:59.957 --> 20:01.991
Susan ross
is going to stomp her.

20:01.993 --> 20:03.359
<i>Susan ross</i>
<i>is far too classy a lady</i>

20:03.361 --> 20:04.960
<i>To make hay</i>
<i>over this non-scandal.</i>

20:04.962 --> 20:06.428
<i>Hollis doyle,</i>
<i>on the other hand...</i>

20:06.430 --> 20:07.963
<i>Susan ross,</i>
<i>hollis doyle, what--</i>

20:07.965 --> 20:08.998
[ television turns off ]
I'm ruined.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.633
It's over.
I can't come back from this.

20:10.635 --> 20:11.767
How can I
come back from this?

20:11.769 --> 20:12.668
What are we gonna do?

20:12.670 --> 20:14.203
You shouldn't have lied,
mellie!

20:14.205 --> 20:15.704
Nobody told you to lie.

20:15.706 --> 20:18.440
I was trying to improvise,
be folksy --

20:18.442 --> 20:19.441
Woman of the people!

20:19.443 --> 20:20.676
That's what you wanted me
to do!

20:20.678 --> 20:21.944
[ sighs ]

20:22.946 --> 20:24.346
So, what now?

20:24.348 --> 20:25.481
I don't know.

20:25.483 --> 20:26.916
I'm thinking.

20:28.652 --> 20:30.986
This entire mess
is your fault.

20:30.988 --> 20:32.721
I did your ridiculous,
little gettysburger plan,

20:32.723 --> 20:33.722
And it blew up in my face.

20:33.724 --> 20:35.558
Hollis is gonna go to town
on this.

20:35.560 --> 20:37.526
Stop thinking
and start doing!

20:37.528 --> 20:39.295
Fix it, olivia!

20:41.631 --> 20:43.732
[ indistinct conversations ]

20:48.004 --> 20:50.406
Big news.
Cyrus.

20:50.408 --> 20:52.208
I have a source.
Two sources.

20:52.210 --> 20:53.075
What's going on?

20:53.077 --> 20:54.577
Edison davis --
he's running.

20:54.579 --> 20:56.312
Well, he's going to.

20:56.314 --> 20:58.981
His advance team is
scouting a location

20:58.983 --> 21:01.417
For him to announce --
could be soon as today.

21:01.419 --> 21:03.185
We know.
Alex heard last night.

21:03.187 --> 21:05.521
Oh. Well...

21:05.523 --> 21:08.424
We need to adjust our strategy,
get oppo research on this.

21:08.426 --> 21:09.325
Alex is on it.

21:09.327 --> 21:10.926
<i>Alex</i> is on it?

21:10.928 --> 21:13.729
Does alex specialize
in oppo research, too?

21:13.731 --> 21:15.030
[ laughs ]

21:15.032 --> 21:16.832
[ chuckles ]
he's got some good ideas.

21:18.268 --> 21:19.435
Huh.

21:19.437 --> 21:20.769
[ pounds on desk ]

21:25.942 --> 21:28.611
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

21:33.383 --> 21:34.483
[ knock at door ]

21:36.853 --> 21:38.520
Hey.
You all right?

21:38.522 --> 21:41.357
I heard debate prep
was a bit of a bust today.

21:43.593 --> 21:44.660
Are you cheating on me?

21:49.766 --> 21:52.034
Of course not.
Why are you asking that?

21:53.303 --> 21:54.570
You're sure?

21:54.572 --> 21:56.805
You can tell me the truth.

21:56.807 --> 21:58.807
I can take it.

22:05.215 --> 22:08.884
I'm not cheating on you.
That's the truth.

22:11.154 --> 22:13.155
So why did I hear a rumor

22:13.157 --> 22:14.757
That you've been seeing
two women?

22:14.759 --> 22:17.092
I'm a public figure.
You know how it is.

22:17.094 --> 22:19.995
People say all sorts of things
about you that aren't true.

22:19.997 --> 22:22.164
All those late nights
at the office

22:22.166 --> 22:23.666
And last-minute
work obligations...

22:23.668 --> 22:25.501
Are just that --
late nights at the office

22:25.503 --> 22:27.569
And work obligations.

22:27.571 --> 22:29.638
I don't want to be
with anyone else.

22:29.640 --> 22:31.674
It's you -- only you.

22:33.977 --> 22:37.479
Besides, I barely had
enough game to seduce you.

22:37.481 --> 22:39.014
I'm not smooth enough
to have an affair.

22:39.016 --> 22:40.916
Right?

22:40.918 --> 22:43.152
Do you still want me
to come up on-stage?

22:43.154 --> 22:45.521
If there are rumors out there,
I'd understand --

22:45.523 --> 22:47.222
No. Of course
I want you up there.

22:55.131 --> 22:57.499
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

22:57.501 --> 23:00.369
[ liquid pouring ]

23:00.371 --> 23:01.737
Thank you.

23:03.106 --> 23:07.843
I must say, your, um, --
your voicemail surprised me.

23:07.845 --> 23:11.013
There was
a note of helplessness --

23:11.015 --> 23:13.982
A daughter who needs her daddy
to make her boo-boo go away.

23:13.984 --> 23:16.618
You gonna tell me
what's going on?

23:16.620 --> 23:17.853
I got a visit yesterday

23:17.855 --> 23:19.988
From frankie vargas's
brother.
Mm-hmm.

23:19.990 --> 23:21.323
He offered me
dirt on susan ross

23:21.325 --> 23:22.691
If I gave him
dirt on edison.

23:22.693 --> 23:24.493
I didn't think I needed it,
so I sent him packing.

23:24.495 --> 23:25.994
And then?

23:25.996 --> 23:28.731
And then my candidate
announced to the world

23:28.733 --> 23:31.133
In the middle of a gettysburger
that she was a big phony,

23:31.135 --> 23:33.869
So now, instead of being
neck-and-neck with susan,

23:33.871 --> 23:36.405
We're polling a distant third
behind her and hollis.

23:40.577 --> 23:43.245
I should take the dirt,
shouldn't I?

23:45.715 --> 23:47.316
[ sighs ]

23:47.318 --> 23:49.017
Of course I should.

23:49.019 --> 23:51.687
It's stupid
I'm even asking.

23:51.689 --> 23:53.522
I mean, let's be honest,

23:53.524 --> 23:57.226
I could've invited a friend over
and sought their opinion,

23:57.228 --> 23:58.761
But instead I asked you.

23:58.763 --> 23:59.895
[ chuckles ]

24:02.031 --> 24:05.601
I brought you here because
I've already decided to do it,

24:05.603 --> 24:08.437
And I want you
to give me permission.

24:08.439 --> 24:09.705
So, go ahead.

24:09.707 --> 24:12.007
Give me
your speech about power

24:12.009 --> 24:14.343
And how the only person I need
to be loyal to is myself.

24:14.345 --> 24:17.112
Tell me that friendship
is a hindrance to greatness

24:17.114 --> 24:19.014
And that I should do
whatever has to be done

24:19.016 --> 24:21.250
To get my candidate
elected.

24:21.252 --> 24:23.952
Say those
[chuckling] things, please.

24:26.556 --> 24:28.023
Tell me
what I need to hear

24:28.025 --> 24:29.858
So that I can stop wasting time
and get back to work.

24:32.529 --> 24:34.530
Let me
ask you something.

24:34.532 --> 24:36.965
Back during
the impeachment hearings,

24:36.967 --> 24:38.901
When the public
was asking for your head --

24:38.903 --> 24:42.404
Who came to your rescue
and sang your praises
on national television?

24:42.406 --> 24:43.405
Edison.

24:43.407 --> 24:44.706
Whose engagement ring
did you return

24:44.708 --> 24:47.075
Because he was the head
of the senate intel committee

24:47.077 --> 24:48.777
And your father
felt threatened by him?

24:48.779 --> 24:50.279
This isn't the speech
I was asking for.

24:50.281 --> 24:54.049
This man has been
nothing but nice to you.

24:54.051 --> 24:56.251
[ sighs ]
I get that, but I --

24:56.253 --> 24:58.220
But what?

24:58.222 --> 25:01.557
You've played dirty before?
Poisoned a few arrows?

25:01.559 --> 25:04.960
Of course you have.

25:04.962 --> 25:06.562
But that was always at the
expense of someone you loathed.

25:06.564 --> 25:09.131
You were robin hood,

25:09.133 --> 25:10.666
Stealing from the rich
and giving to the poor.

25:10.668 --> 25:11.733
This would be different.

25:11.735 --> 25:14.002
This would be hurting
someone you respect,

25:14.004 --> 25:15.170
Someone
who is innocent,

25:15.172 --> 25:18.740
Someone who has never
done anything to harm you.

25:18.742 --> 25:22.845
You'd no longer be robin hood,
olivia, you'd be --

25:22.847 --> 25:24.246
You.

25:29.486 --> 25:33.322
The reason
mellie grant imploded today

25:33.324 --> 25:36.492
Is because you were trying to
make her something she wasn't.

25:38.495 --> 25:40.496
I'd hate to see you make
the same mistake with yourself.

25:55.144 --> 25:56.478
Finally,
after running into him again,

25:56.480 --> 25:57.813
He asked me out,
and here we are.

25:57.815 --> 25:59.348
Wow.
That happened so fast?

25:59.350 --> 26:01.216
Yeah. I don't know
if I believe in fate,

26:01.218 --> 26:03.051
But if it wasn't fate,
it was pretty darn close.

26:03.053 --> 26:04.820
Oh, god.
I envy that.

26:04.822 --> 26:08.056
It's so romantic to just know
after only a few months.

26:08.058 --> 26:09.658
Oh!

26:09.660 --> 26:12.127
I can tell you, he definitely
knows all my secrets.

26:12.129 --> 26:14.830
That's the one drawback
to marrying the head of the nsa.

26:14.832 --> 26:16.498
Those guys
dig pretty deep, huh?

26:16.500 --> 26:17.833
Oh, yeah.

26:17.835 --> 26:19.167
I had to submit
all my tax records,

26:19.169 --> 26:20.636
Bank statements --
what else?

26:20.638 --> 26:21.537
Laptops and stuff?

26:21.539 --> 26:22.704
Sure.

26:22.706 --> 26:24.006
They did
a full background check.

26:24.008 --> 26:25.007
[ chuckles ]

26:25.009 --> 26:26.842
Okay, now,
that is not romantic.

26:26.844 --> 26:29.011
No, not at all.
But it's his job.

26:29.013 --> 26:30.979
Neither of us
really had a choice.

26:30.981 --> 26:32.180
Mm-hmm.

26:32.182 --> 26:33.682
He really cares
about america.

26:33.684 --> 26:34.883
Yeah.

26:36.519 --> 26:37.753
Man: [ over television ]
<i>then I guess it's susan ross',</i>

26:37.755 --> 26:38.754
<i>'cause mellie --</i>
<i>[ television turns off ]</i>

26:38.756 --> 26:40.088
What'd you find
on edison davis?

26:40.090 --> 26:42.357
Nothing.
He's clean as a whistle.

26:42.359 --> 26:43.926
That's impossible!

26:43.928 --> 26:46.929
The man's from florida,
for god's sake!

26:46.931 --> 26:48.830
That's 65,000 square miles
of corruption.

26:48.832 --> 26:50.265
Nobody escapes that.
He has.

26:50.267 --> 26:53.235
Well, he's not our main concern,
but keep looking.

26:53.237 --> 26:54.503
We have to cover our bases.

26:54.505 --> 26:55.671
Do you need to get home?

26:55.673 --> 26:57.506
No.

26:57.508 --> 26:58.774
Not yet.

26:58.776 --> 27:01.543
Hey,
what about alex vargas?

27:01.545 --> 27:02.911
What have you
found on him?
Still working on it.

27:02.913 --> 27:03.779
Put your coat back on.

27:03.781 --> 27:05.380
What?

27:05.382 --> 27:06.949
Put your coat back on,
and don't come back to me

27:06.951 --> 27:09.384
Until you have something
on alex vargas.

27:09.386 --> 27:13.121
Alex vargas is a hiccup.
You've dealt with far worse.

27:13.123 --> 27:15.190
He's not just somebody
who wants my job.

27:15.192 --> 27:17.726
He's family -- blood.
Blood's different.

27:17.728 --> 27:20.629
Blood gets rewarded for the
simple fact that they're blood.

27:20.631 --> 27:23.365
Trust me.

27:23.367 --> 27:27.269
I'm one brotherly heart-to-heart
away from being demoted

27:27.271 --> 27:29.571
To frankie vargas'
body man.

27:29.573 --> 27:30.806
[ door opens, closes ]

27:30.808 --> 27:33.108
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

27:33.110 --> 27:34.109
[ door opens ]

27:34.111 --> 27:35.577
Pants.

27:35.579 --> 27:36.712
What?
[ door closes ]

27:36.714 --> 27:38.213
Remove your pants,
david.

27:38.215 --> 27:40.115
I was about
to come see you.

27:40.117 --> 27:41.950
Well, now you're gonna come over
to that couch,

27:41.952 --> 27:43.719
And I'm gonna
sit on top of you.

27:43.721 --> 27:45.253
And I'm gonna
move up and down

27:45.255 --> 27:47.556
Until your eyes roll back
in your head.

27:47.558 --> 27:49.458
Is this because susan's been
doing better in the debate prep

27:49.460 --> 27:50.759
Since I talked to her?

27:50.761 --> 27:53.228
Yep. Whatever you said to her
worked like a charm.

27:53.230 --> 27:54.930
She's back on her game
big-time.

27:54.932 --> 27:56.732
This is your reward.

27:56.734 --> 27:58.800
Now, I can either pull
your pants down for you,

27:58.802 --> 27:59.801
Or you can do it yourself.

27:59.803 --> 28:00.636
But they need
to come off.

28:00.638 --> 28:02.170
I can't do it.

28:02.172 --> 28:04.006
Well, it's really easy,
but, fine, I'll do it.

28:04.008 --> 28:05.173
I mean I can't do <i>this.</i>

28:05.175 --> 28:06.942
Do what?
This thing -- us.

28:06.944 --> 28:08.010
I can't do us.

28:08.012 --> 28:10.112
[ sighs ] don't play
hard to get, david.

28:10.114 --> 28:11.747
It might be a turn-on for you,
but it's not for me.

28:11.749 --> 28:13.482
Now, heels or no heels?

28:13.484 --> 28:15.450
I mean it, liz.
We're done.

28:15.452 --> 28:17.653
You're serious?

28:17.655 --> 28:19.087
You are dumping <i>me?</i>

28:19.089 --> 28:20.322
Yes.

28:20.324 --> 28:22.124
[ sighs ]

28:22.126 --> 28:23.492
You're sure about that?

28:23.494 --> 28:24.960
Yes?

28:24.962 --> 28:25.827
No.

28:25.829 --> 28:27.362
That's not
how this works.

28:27.364 --> 28:28.597
No.

28:28.599 --> 28:31.133
I'm in love
with susan ross.

28:31.135 --> 28:33.969
She's a muppet!
Elizabeth --

28:33.971 --> 28:35.003
Not even
one of the main ones.

28:35.005 --> 28:36.304
Liz --
she'd be way in the back.

28:36.306 --> 28:37.773
They'd only let her
play tambourine

28:37.775 --> 28:38.640
In their little
muppet band.

28:38.642 --> 28:40.175
Enough!

28:40.177 --> 28:41.943
Do not talk about susan
like that anymore.

28:43.146 --> 28:44.880
I was nice to you.
I liked you.

28:44.882 --> 28:47.182
I wasn't sleeping with
anyone else this entire time.

28:47.184 --> 28:48.383
Look...

28:48.385 --> 28:49.217
I'm sorry.

28:50.520 --> 28:51.853
[ scoffs ]

28:55.024 --> 28:56.625
Enjoy the minor leagues.

28:59.395 --> 29:00.962
[ door opens ]

29:02.498 --> 29:03.732
They're using her
for her bank accounts.

29:03.734 --> 29:06.134
Vanessa --
she mentioned something

29:06.136 --> 29:08.236
About jake asking for all
of her bank-account numbers,

29:08.238 --> 29:09.705
Which I thought was weird,
because I was pretty sure

29:09.707 --> 29:11.640
The nsa doesn't require
financial information

29:11.642 --> 29:12.841
In their standard
spouse-registration form.

29:12.843 --> 29:13.742
So I double-checked,
and I was right.

29:13.744 --> 29:14.576
Quinn, slow down.
Really?

29:14.578 --> 29:15.744
Yeah.
You sure?

29:15.746 --> 29:17.312
Because you usually
don't want me to...

29:17.314 --> 29:18.847
Okay.

29:18.849 --> 29:22.718
So, uh, someone accessed
all of vanessa's accounts

29:22.720 --> 29:24.352
And cloned their reverse
promontory points,

29:24.354 --> 29:25.754
Which allowed them
to funnel money

29:25.756 --> 29:27.355
Through incremental
proxy withdrawals,

29:27.357 --> 29:28.156
And then --
sorry.
You were right.

29:28.158 --> 29:29.324
Get to the point.

29:29.326 --> 29:31.593
Jake's using vanessa's money
to fund a super pac.

29:31.595 --> 29:33.428
A super pac?

29:33.430 --> 29:34.930
Do you know
which candidate it's for?

29:37.033 --> 29:40.035
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

29:40.037 --> 29:41.803
[ door opens,
footsteps approach ]

29:43.239 --> 29:44.940
Olivia.

29:44.942 --> 29:46.074
Twice in one week.

29:46.076 --> 29:47.609
I should run for president
more often.

29:47.611 --> 29:49.111
I need to talk to you
about my father.

29:49.113 --> 29:50.946
Eli?
Okay, I'm listening.

29:52.682 --> 29:55.350
You only know him

29:55.352 --> 29:58.220
As the man who fell from grace
at the smithsonian,

29:58.222 --> 29:59.688
But he's actually
much more powerful than that

29:59.690 --> 30:01.556
And much more dangerous.

30:01.558 --> 30:03.024
How so?

30:03.026 --> 30:04.860
I think he's secretly funding
your super pac,

30:04.862 --> 30:06.194
Which means that,
at some point,

30:06.196 --> 30:07.896
He's going to ask you
for a favor.

30:07.898 --> 30:10.899
And, trust me, you do not want
to do any favors for that man.

30:10.901 --> 30:15.203
Or what?
He'll do me terrible harm?

30:20.109 --> 30:21.877
He's already reached out to you,
hasn't he?

30:24.947 --> 30:27.282
When a man of his stature,
his accomplishments,

30:27.284 --> 30:29.618
Tells you that he can make you
the next president,

30:29.620 --> 30:30.952
That's hard to turn down.

30:30.954 --> 30:33.388
Do you know
what he's about?

30:33.390 --> 30:34.656
The things he's done?

30:34.658 --> 30:35.924
You forget
that I'm the head

30:35.926 --> 30:37.092
Of the senate intelligence
committee, olivia.

30:37.094 --> 30:39.327
Edison, you don't want him
anywhere near you.

30:39.329 --> 30:42.631
You know many things,
olivia.

30:42.633 --> 30:44.833
But here's something
that you may not know.

30:44.835 --> 30:46.401
The senate
is a gilded cage --

30:46.403 --> 30:48.670
A place of great comfort
and wonderful perks,

30:48.672 --> 30:50.071
Where you think that
you're making a difference,

30:50.073 --> 30:51.273
But you're not.

30:51.275 --> 30:52.674
It's just you
and 99 others

30:52.676 --> 30:54.609
Grimly reminding yourselves
every day

30:54.611 --> 30:58.413
That the only way out of this,
the <i>only</i> way to make your mark,

30:58.415 --> 30:59.648
Is to be president.

30:59.650 --> 31:03.084
You're getting into bed
with a monster.

31:03.086 --> 31:05.987
Correction -- I'm getting into
bed with a monster's father.

31:09.091 --> 31:13.328
Anyway, thanks so much
for coming by.

31:23.506 --> 31:24.840
Hollis doyle taking the lead
in the latest polls,

31:24.842 --> 31:26.141
Securing the center podium
for tomorrow's debate.

31:26.143 --> 31:27.876
I'd say this is quite
a surprising turn of events.

31:27.878 --> 31:29.611
You know, brooke,
I'm gonna go on the record

31:29.613 --> 31:31.346
And say that
I am <i>not</i> surprised.

31:31.348 --> 31:32.948
Come on.

31:32.950 --> 31:34.616
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

31:36.786 --> 31:38.186
Fitz:
You're still here?

31:38.188 --> 31:40.889
Oh, mr. President.
Hello.

31:40.891 --> 31:43.992
You should go home, susan --
get a good night's rest.

31:43.994 --> 31:46.561
I don't think I'd be able to
sleep tonight if I tried, sir.

31:47.830 --> 31:50.799
You know,
I'm sorry about today.

31:50.801 --> 31:52.734
You don't need to be sorry
about anything.

31:52.736 --> 31:55.136
No, I do.
I was off my game.

31:55.138 --> 31:57.005
I disappointed you.
I could tell.

31:57.007 --> 31:59.407
Because I was dealing with
a silly, little personal issue.

31:59.409 --> 32:01.409
But I'm back now.
I am all good.

32:01.411 --> 32:02.410
Glad to hear it.

32:02.412 --> 32:03.645
So, go ahead.

32:03.647 --> 32:06.081
Ask me something.
Anything.

32:06.083 --> 32:08.516
National security,
minimum wage, gun reform.

32:08.518 --> 32:10.819
You got questions?
I got answers.

32:12.221 --> 32:14.489
[ chuckling ] all right.

32:14.491 --> 32:15.390
Let's see...

32:15.392 --> 32:18.426
Vice president ross,
as president,

32:18.428 --> 32:19.828
How would you
work to solve

32:19.830 --> 32:21.830
Our nation's
looming federal deficit?

32:30.239 --> 32:31.506
Susan?

32:31.508 --> 32:33.241
Why did you
cheat on your wife?

32:33.243 --> 32:34.876
What?

32:34.878 --> 32:37.879
Do you know
why you cheated?

32:37.881 --> 32:39.080
On someone
you supposedly loved.

32:41.217 --> 32:42.217
Why do you ask?

32:42.219 --> 32:44.853
I'm sorry for asking.
It's just --

32:44.855 --> 32:46.388
Is this a part
of your debate prep?

32:46.390 --> 32:48.556
Actually, yes,
mr. President.

32:48.558 --> 32:49.624
Why I cheated?

32:49.626 --> 32:51.293
Why does anyone cheat?

32:51.295 --> 32:53.895
Oh.
I'm the expert now?

32:53.897 --> 32:56.431
Well,
you're pretty good at it.

32:56.433 --> 32:58.433
[ chuckles ]

32:58.435 --> 33:01.136
[ scoffs ] I don't want to be
one of those stupid women

33:01.138 --> 33:02.971
Who believes
whatever a guy says

33:02.973 --> 33:05.373
Just because her self-esteem
can't handle the truth.

33:05.375 --> 33:08.877
But part of me --
I believe him.

33:08.879 --> 33:11.313
I believe he really loves me,
so...

33:11.315 --> 33:14.316
[ sighs ]

33:14.318 --> 33:17.652
People cheat
for different reasons.

33:17.654 --> 33:19.654
So I can't tell you
exactly why people cheat.

33:19.656 --> 33:20.855
But I can tell you this --

33:23.326 --> 33:27.062
If you feel like he's cheating,
then he probably is.

33:31.567 --> 33:32.567
[ sighs ]

33:32.569 --> 33:33.868
[ exhales sharply ]

33:36.005 --> 33:36.871
[ inhales deeply ]

33:42.511 --> 33:44.980
The figures
speak for themselves.

33:44.982 --> 33:47.148
When unemployment drops,
our deficit drops.

33:47.150 --> 33:49.851
The key to reducing
our national debt isn't

33:49.853 --> 33:53.321
About some shortsighted strategy
cooked up by senator grant,

33:53.323 --> 33:56.191
Or a useless, little band-aid
slapped on by mr. Doyle.

33:56.193 --> 33:59.294
It's about putting people
to work, plain and simple.

33:59.296 --> 34:01.863
As your president,
that's exactly what I'll do.

34:05.968 --> 34:08.003
Good night,
mr. President.

34:08.005 --> 34:09.237
I should probably
get some sleep.

34:15.644 --> 34:17.112
<i>[ camera shutter clicking ]</i>

34:17.114 --> 34:18.480
I'm trying to tell you

34:18.482 --> 34:21.116
About a potentially fundamental
human-rights case,

34:21.118 --> 34:22.350
And all you can say is --
you're so beautiful,

34:22.352 --> 34:23.818
I can hardly hear the words
coming out of your mouth.

34:23.820 --> 34:24.919
[ cellphone beeps ]

34:27.456 --> 34:29.024
Work?
Can't say.

34:35.698 --> 34:37.332
[ sighs ]

34:37.334 --> 34:38.333
Sorry to interrupt.

34:38.335 --> 34:39.567
I doubt that.

34:41.404 --> 34:43.938
What's up, liv?
What do you want?

34:53.015 --> 34:54.649
[ bettye lavette's
"round midnight" playing ]

34:54.651 --> 34:56.117
[ lock clicks ]

34:57.987 --> 35:01.489
â™ª it begins to tell

35:03.392 --> 35:04.526
â™ª round midnight

35:04.528 --> 35:06.594
Vanessa's right outside.

35:06.596 --> 35:08.530
â™ª round midnight

35:08.532 --> 35:10.231
Does she know how you're using
